Sentencas: The development of technologies used to prepare thin electrolyte films will stimulate the application of electrolyte supported SOFCs since thin electrolyte films typically have low ohmic resistances and good electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: This paper presents a novel method for the preparation of thin electrolyte films for yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ)-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) via dry pressing/heating/quenching/calcining.
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: The thicknesses of the as-prepared YSZ films were as low as 78 mu m, which is significantly thinner than those prepared using a traditional method (greater than 200 mu m) via dry pressing/calcining/polishing.
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: More importantly, the preparation process was quicker.
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: Using this novel method, a YSZ-supported cell with a configuration of (La0.6Sr0.4)(0.9)Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (LSCF)-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta(SDC)/SDC/YSZ/SDC/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta(BSCF)-SDC was fabricated and tested.
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: The results showed promising electrochemical performance and a peak power density of 0.64 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C was obtained, which was much higher than the cell fabricated using the traditional method (0.29 W cm(-2)).
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: The ohmic resistance (R-O) at 850 degrees C is 0.19 Omega cm(2), which is much lower than that of the cell fabricated using the traditional method (0.33 Omega cm(2)) at an identical temperature.
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: The modified method described in this work is shown to be a promising technique to prepare thin electrolyte films for high-performance, electrolyte-supported SOFCs.
Titulo: Preparation of thin electrolyte film via dry pressing/heating/ quenching/calcining for electrolyte-supported SOFCs
